# SwissKit / Kagglebase Agent Rules
This project is an ML boilerplate repository designed for efficient data processing, modeling, and experimentation.
Please refer to `agents.md` in the root of the workspace for comprehensive architectural guidelines, standards, and how to execute scripts.

# Core tenets
- Maintain single-responsibility scripts in `src/`.
- Append new model architectures strictly via `src/model_dispatcher.py`.
- Ensure all models natively follow the scikit-learn API structure (use wrapper classes if introducing PyTorch/Keras models).
- Read from `input/` and write trained output only to `models/`.
